document_data.History:
In [[1479 DR]] Julen was sent into the jungles of Southern [[Faerûn]] with the Travelers branch of the Serrat clan to assist with the [[terazul]] harvest.  While in the jungle, Zaltys, a [[ranger]] and accomplished archer, taught him some of the basics of forest craft.

Zaltys learned that her birth clan may not have been slaughtered but rather imprisoned in the Underdark and decided to venture underground to find survivors.{{Cite digital book/Venom in Her Veins/Kindle|1405}}  Julen accompanied her and was captured by [[derro]].{{Cite digital book/Venom in Her Veins/Kindle|1557}}  Julen escaped and was found by Zaltys and together the two traveled to the derro settlement.

At the derro settlement they confronted the derro leader the [[Iraska|Slime King]] and she spiked Julen's water with a poison.{{Cite digital book/Venom in Her Veins/Kindle|3139}}  Since Julen was immune to many poisons he shrugged it off and used a magic [[fey]] dagger to entwine the Slime King in vines.  Julen and Zaltys raced to the slave pens and freed the slaves.

Meanwhile, Zaltys adopted mother [[Alaia Serrat]] and her guard captain [[Krailash]] had heard a psychic sending from Zaltys and had made their way to the derro village.  Krailash sacrificed himself by pushing the Slime King through a portal to the [[Far Realm]], sealing the portal.{{Cite digital book/Venom in Her Veins/Kindle|3605}}

Julen's adventure into the Underdark convinced him that working underground wasn't for him so, rather than working for his brother trading with dwarves, he decided to run away from his family and travel with Zaltys through the Realms.{{Cite digital book/Venom in Her Veins/Kindle|3804}}
